    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-08-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-08-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="417"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-08-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 26, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2045.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the due receipt
                    of your printed instruction<note n="a" xml:id="d417fna">Printed under Austria,
                            <ref target="#pg_42">page 42</ref>.</note> of the 11th instant, relative
                    to the treatment of Jews in the Kingdom of Roumania, and to inform you that in
                    compliance therewith the contents of the same were communicated to Baron von
                    Richthofen, the imperial secretary of state for foreign affairs (who had just
                    returned to Berlin and resumed charge at the foreign office), and a copy of the
                    same left with him this afternoon. Baron Richthofen said that he would “give the
                    matter such consideration as its importance deserves.”</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <p>For Ambassador White:</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John B. Jackson</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of Embassy.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
